    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7069" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄφρα</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">while, until, in
            order that.</span>— (1) temporal; once as adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">for a while,
            some time;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄφρα μέν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.547</span></i>; elsewhere conj., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">as long as,
            while</span>, freq. w. correl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τόφρα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 4.220</span></i>; then
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">until</span>, with ref. to the past or the fut., and with
          the appropriate constructions, <i><span class="en">Il.
            5.557</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.82</span></i>.—(2) final
          conj., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">in order that, that</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.147</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 1.85</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 24.334</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
